For the LC 4% and Taiwan Credit Default datasets, the group quality metric $  Q  $ initially returned NaN values for certain Owen-based explanation methods when agglomerative clustering produced a single feature group. This was addressed by implementing a robust fallback in the compute_Q function that assigns $  Q = 1.0  $ (perfect grouping quality) in single-group cases, ensuring all Owen variants now have valid numeric $  Q  $ values in the result files and fully populated points in the Q vs I plots
